<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-14T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/4607: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Personal Representative of the President</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-14T12:00:00-05:00">January 14,
                                1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>14. My No. 12, January 14, 3 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.</hi>] I think
                            it is safe to say that a government headed by Mendieta and supported by
                            Batista will represent a majority of the Cuban people: both of them
                            without question are extremely popular in very different sectors of the
                            public.</p>
                        <p>I again respectfully urge immediate action in order to avert a
                            catastrophe: the only other section of the public which has any chance
                            of reaching power at this time is the extreme left.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>